From: rich@mulvey.com (Rich Mulvey)
Subject: Re: dual monitors?
Date: Sat, 11 Sep 1993 15:41:57 EDT

jkonrath@bronze.ucs.indiana.edu (Jon Konrath) writes:

> 
> Does anyone know if there is a way to use dual monitors in X and what
> hardware is needed to do this?  I'm going to upgrade and was thinking
> of getting some use out of my old monitor....
>

Yup - I'm doing it here.  One of the monitors needs to be an MDA/Hercules,
while the other uses any of the color cards.  Simply pop both of the
adapters into your system, modify the XConfig so that you include
HGC2, and away you go.  :-)

BTW - I'm using the mono server.  I don't know if this will work with the
color server, as well.

- Rich

